#compdef ssh-tpm-keygen
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# Foxboron/ssh-tpm-agent cmd/ssh-tpm-keygen/main.go —
#   usage at lines 33-88 (the const usage block with 7
#     invocation patterns)
#   parse_argv at lines 506-524 (19 flag.StringVar/BoolVar/
#     IntVar calls)
#   hierarchy + parent-handle enum strings at usage lines
#     56-66 (owner/o, endorsement/e, null/n, platform/p)
#   key-type defaults at usage lines 47-50 (rsa: 2048,
#     ecdsa: 256/384/521)
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# ssh-tpm-keygen is the **TPM sealed-key generator** —
# creates SSH private keys INSIDE the Trusted Platform Module
# and writes them to `.tpm`-suffixed files.  Sister tool to
# ssh-tpm-add (loads them into the agent) and ssh-tpm-
# hostkeys (lists agent-provided host keys).  Compatible with
# the OpenSSH key file format conventions (the public key
# half is written as a normal `.pub` file).
#
# Critical extraction note: ssh-tpm-keygen has the LARGEST
# flag surface of the ssh-tpm-* family — 19 flag declarations
# at main.go:506-524.  The 7 invocation patterns at the
# usage block correspond to 7 different workflows:
#   1. `ssh-tpm-keygen`                       (interactive create)
#   2. `ssh-tpm-keygen --wrap --wrap-with`    (wrap-for-remote)
#   3. `ssh-tpm-keygen --import keyfile`      (import existing)
#   4. `ssh-tpm-keygen --print-pubkey`        (print pubkey)
#   5. `ssh-tpm-keygen --supported`           (list TPM caps)
#   6. `ssh-tpm-keygen -p -f -N -P`           (change passphrase)
#   7. `ssh-tpm-keygen -A -f --hierarchy`     (generate host keys)
#
# Critical extraction note: 4 flags have BOTH short and long
# forms (registered via TWO flag calls each):
#   -o / --owner-password    (main.go:506-507)
#   -I / --import            (main.go:513-514)
# The remaining 15 are single-form only.  Completion lists
# both forms via the mutex `(-o --owner-password)` syntax.
#
# Critical extraction note: hierarchy + parent-handle accept
# **4-value enums with short aliases**:
#   owner       (alias: o)   default for parent-handle
#   endorsement (alias: e)
#   null        (alias: n)
#   platform    (alias: p)
# Each parameter accepts EITHER the full name OR the
# single-char alias.  Completion offers all 8 strings.

local -a hierarchies=(
  'owner:owner hierarchy (default; user-controllable)'
  'o:short for owner'
  'endorsement:endorsement hierarchy (TPM-vendor-signed)'
  'e:short for endorsement'
  'null:null hierarchy (volatile; clears on TPM reset)'
  'n:short for null'
  'platform:platform hierarchy (UEFI-firmware-controlled)'
  'p:short for platform'
)

_arguments \
  '(-o --owner-password)'{-o,--owner-password}'[ask for the TPM owner password (required for hierarchy=endorsement/platform)]' \
  '-C+[provide a comment with the key (default: user@host)]:comment:' \
  '-f+[output keyfile path]:file:_files' \
  '-N+[new passphrase for the key]:passphrase:' \
  '-t+[key type to create (default ecdsa)]:type:(ecdsa rsa)' \
  '-b+[number of bits (rsa: 2048; ecdsa: 256/384/521)]:bits:(256 384 521 2048 3072 4096)' \
  '(-I --import)'{-I+,--import=}'[import an existing SSH private key into the TPM]:file:_files' \
  '-p[change the keyfile passphrase (use with -f -N -P)]' \
  '-P+[old passphrase for the keyfile]:passphrase:' \
  '-swtpm[use software TPM (swtpm) instead of actual hardware TPM]' \
  '-A[generate host keys for all key types (rsa + ecdsa)]' \
  '-supported[list the supported keys of the local TPM]' \
  '-print-pubkey=[print the public key for a given TPM private key file]:file:_files -g "*.tpm"' \
  '-wrap=[an SSH key to wrap for transport to a remote machine]:file:_files' \
  '-wrap-with=[parent key to wrap the SSH key with]:file:_files' \
  '-parent-handle=[parent for the TPM key (hierarchy or persistent handle; default: owner)]:handle:(owner o endorsement e null n platform p)' \
  '-hierarchy=[hierarchy to create the persistent public key under (only with -A)]:hierarchy:(owner o endorsement e null n platform p)'
